posts.description: During our short stay in Barcelona we saw so many beautiful places that I could be sharing pictures for the next 2 weeks! This is one of the beautiful details of @elnacionalbcn, an incredibly beautiful space of 4 different restaurants and 4 bars - all under one roof.

Palau de la Musica Catalana, a place I wanted to visit for a long time, is an amazing example of Catalan Art Nouveau architecture. Many thanks to @palaumusicacat and @casabatllo for giving us a private tour of the building and the opportunity to see the concert rehearsal and then the consent itself in the main hall. If you are in Barcelona, I'd highly recommend to visit either on a guided tour or for a concert.

Hola Barcelona! I'm very excited to be here with @casabatllo for the celebration of Sant Jordi. Casa Battlo is an amazing masterpiece by Antoni Gaudi, whose creations are always inspired by nature. For this weekend only Casa Battlo is decorated with roses that is part of Sant Jordi tradition - men give roses to women and women give books to men. #casabattlo #mesqueunarosa

Still thinking about yesterday's flower workshop with @londonflowerschool and @wagnerjk - I learned how to make natural flower arrangements which appeared to be very therapeutic! I got to take those gorgeous flowers home with me and surprisingly they've survived the tube ride very well! 
In other news @creatingforgood creative conference programme is now published on the website and there will be so many interesting workshops! All the profits will go to support @womenforwomenuk. Please let me know if any of you is planning to come - would be great to see you there!
Another place, not everyone knows about - library at @vamuseum. It's a very beautiful space and anyone can apply for a reader's ticket free of charge! Love V&A!

It's been almost a week since I'm back and I have just shared my favourite viewpoints and coffee shops of Auckland on my blog (link in bio). Another post about other amazing spots on the North Island coming soon so stay tuned!
